Three students die due to food poisoning in Karnataka boarding school 
9-3-2017 
A case has been registered in Karnataka after three students died due to food poisoning at a boarding school in Tumkur.

The incident took place at Vidhyavaridhi International Boarding school in Tumkurâ€™s Chikkanayakana Halli.

The students who died due to food poisoning were identified as Shanthamurthy, Aakansha Pallakki and Shreyas.

One more student and a guard are currently undergoing treatment.

The boarding school belongs to former MLA Kiran Kumar.

A case was filed at Huliyar police station, and investigation is underway.

